      If the passed in value is a UUID, calls getConceptVersion(UUID) Next, if no hit, if the passed in value is parseable as a long, treats it as an SCTID and converts that to UUID and then calls getConceptVersion(UUID) Next, if no hit, if the passed in value is parseable as a int, calls getConceptVersion(int)
      static void lookupIdentifier(String identifier, ConceptLookupCallback callback, Integer callId)
      If the passed in value is a UUID, calls getConceptVersion(UUID) Next, if no hit, if the passed in value is parseable as a long, treats it as an SCTID and converts that to UUID and then calls getConceptVersion(UUID) Next, if no hit, if the passed in value is parseable as a int, calls getConceptVersion(int) All done in a background thread, method returns immediately

      • lookupIdentifier

        public static org.ihtsdo.otf.tcc.api.concept.ConceptVersionBI lookupIdentifier(String identifier)
        If the passed in value is a UUID, calls getConceptVersion(UUID) Next, if no hit, if the passed in value is parseable as a long, treats it as an SCTID and converts that to UUID and then calls getConceptVersion(UUID) Next, if no hit, if the passed in value is parseable as a int, calls getConceptVersion(int)

      • lookupIdentifier

        public static void lookupIdentifier(String identifier,
                                    ConceptLookupCallback callback,
                                    Integer callId)
        If the passed in value is a UUID, calls getConceptVersion(UUID) Next, if no hit, if the passed in value is parseable as a long, treats it as an SCTID and converts that to UUID and then calls getConceptVersion(UUID) Next, if no hit, if the passed in value is parseable as a int, calls getConceptVersion(int) All done in a background thread, method returns immediately
        Parameters:
        identifier - - what to search for
        callback - - who to inform when lookup completes
        callId - - An arbitrary identifier that will be returned to the caller when this completes
